Simple file word-counter |\\n\",","    \"| 3 | `argparse` — Argument Parsing | Log file analyser |\\n\",","    \"| 4 | Subcommands | Git-style project manager |\\n\",","    \"| 5 | stdin / stdout / stderr | Unix-style text pipeline tool |\\n\",","    \"| 6 | Exit Codes \u0026 Error Handling | Deployment health-checker |\\n\",","    \"| 7 | Config Files \u0026 Environment Variables | API key manager |\\n\",","    \"| 8 | Progress \u0026 Rich Output | Bulk file processor |\\n\",","    \"| 9 | Packaging \u0026 Entry Points | Installable CLI tool |\\n\",","    \"| 10 | Mini-Project | `devkit` — a developer utilities CLI |\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"---\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### ⚙️ Prerequisites\\n\",","    \"- Python 3.8+\\n\",","    \"- Standard library only for Sections 1–8 (no installs)\\n\",","    \"- Section 9 uses `pip` (standard)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 1 — Anatomy of a CLI Program\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### What makes a program a \\\"CLI tool\\\"?\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"A command-line program is any program invoked from a terminal with arguments, that reads from stdin / files, writes results to stdout, and signals success or failure via an **exit code**.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"$ myprogram --input data.csv --output report.txt --verbose\\n\",","    \"  └──────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────┘\\n\",","    \"  command     flag + value      flag + value          flag\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### The standard layout of a Python CLI script\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"myapp/\\n\",","    \"├── myapp/\\n\",","    \"│   ├── __init__.py\\n\",","    \"│   ├── cli.py          ← argument parsing, entry point\\n\",","    \"│   ├── core.py         ← business logic (pure functions, no I/O)\\n\",","    \"│   └── utils.py        ← shared helpers\\n\",","    \"├── tests/\\n\",","    \"├── setup.py  (or pyproject.toml)\\n\",","    \"└── README.md\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"The golden rule: **keep business logic separate from I/O**. This makes your CLI testable.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### The `if __name__ == '__main__'` guard\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# anatomy_demo.py  — the skeleton every CLI script should start with\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"import sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Business logic lives in functions, not at module level ──\\n\",","    \"def greet(name: str, loud: bool = False) -\u003e str:\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Pure function — no I/O, easy to test.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    msg = f\\\"Hello, {name}!\\\"\\n\",","    \"    return msg.upper() if loud else msg\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def main():\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Entry point — handles I/O and argument wrangling.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    name = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) \u003e 1 else \\\"World\\\"\\n\",","    \"    loud = \\\"--loud\\\" in sys.argv\\n\",","    \"    print(greet(name, loud))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── This guard means: only run main() when executed directly,\\n\",","    \"#    not when imported as a module by another script. ─────────\\n\",","    \"if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"    main()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── In a notebook we call directly: ─────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"print(greet(\\\"Alice\\\"))\\n\",","    \"print(greet(\\\"Alice\\\", loud=True))\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ Notice how greet() is pure — no sys.argv, no print() inside it.\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"   This means we can unit-test it without running the whole CLI.\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Write the file to disk and run it as a real CLI process\\n\",","    \"import subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def greet(name, loud=False):\\n\",","    \"        msg = f\\\"Hello, {name}!\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return msg.upper() if loud else msg\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        name = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) \u003e 1 else \\\"World\\\"\\n\",","    \"        loud = \\\"--loud\\\" in sys.argv\\n\",","    \"        print(greet(name, loud))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/greet.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"for cmd in [\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/greet.py\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/greet.py\\\", \\\"Alice\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/greet.py\\\", \\\"Bob\\\", \\\"--loud\\\"],\\n\",","    \"]:\\n\",","    \"    result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"$ {' '.join(cmd[1:])}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  → {result.stdout.strip()}\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 1\\n\",","    \"Write a `farewell.py` script with a `farewell(name, formal=False)` function:\\n\",","    \"- Normal: `\\\"Goodbye, Alice!\\\"`\\n\",","    \"- Formal: `\\\"It was a pleasure, Alice. Farewell.\\\"`\\n\",","    \"- Takes `name` as a positional arg and `--formal` as a flag\\n\",","    \"- Falls back to `\\\"Stranger\\\"` if no name provided\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Your code here — write the script to /tmp/farewell.py then test it\\n\",","    \"import subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def farewell(name, formal=False):\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/farewell.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Test:\\n\",","    \"# subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/farewell.py\\\", \\\"Alice\\\"], ...)\\n\",","    \"# subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/farewell.py\\\", \\\"Alice\\\", \\\"--formal\\\"], ...)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 2 — `sys.argv`: Reading Raw Arguments\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"`sys.argv` is a list where `sys.argv[0]` is the script name and `sys.argv[1:]` are the arguments the user typed.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"$ python counter.py report.txt --min-words 5\\n\",","    \"  sys.argv = ['counter.py', 'report.txt', '--min-words', '5']\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Use `sys.argv` for **very simple** scripts (1–2 arguments). For anything more, use `argparse`.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📄 Scenario: Word-count tool for a writing assistant\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── The CLI script ───────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"wordcount_script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import sys\\n\",","    \"    import os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def count_file(path):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Count words, lines, and characters in a file.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        if not os.path.exists(path):\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: file not found: {path}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"            text = f.read()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        lines = text.splitlines()\\n\",","    \"        words = text.split()\\n\",","    \"        chars = len(text)\\n\",","    \"        return {\\\"lines\\\": len(lines), \\\"words\\\": len(words), \\\"chars\\\": chars, \\\"file\\\": path}\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        # Validate argument count\\n\",","    \"        if len(sys.argv) \u003c 2:\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"Usage: wordcount.py \u003cfile\u003e [file2 ...]\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"  Count words, lines, and characters in text files.\\\")\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(2)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        files = sys.argv[1:]\\n\",","    \"        results = []\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        for path in files:\\n\",","    \"            stats = count_file(path)\\n\",","    \"            results.append(stats)\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {stats['lines']:\u003e6} lines  {stats['words']:\u003e8} words  {stats['chars']:\u003e10} chars   {path}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Print totals if more than one file\\n\",","    \"        if len(results) \u003e 1:\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"-\\\" * 55)\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {sum(r['lines'] for r in results):\u003e6} lines  \\\"\\n\",","    \"                  f\\\"{sum(r['words'] for r in results):\u003e8} words  \\\"\\n\",","    \"                  f\\\"{sum(r['chars'] for r in results):\u003e10} chars   total\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/wordcount.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(wordcount_script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Create sample files\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(\\\"Python is a versatile language.\\\\n\\\" * 10 + \\\"It is used in web, data science, and automation.\\\\n\\\" * 5)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/notes.txt\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(\\\"Meeting notes from Monday.\\\\nAction items:\\\\n- Fix bug\\\\n- Write tests\\\\n- Deploy to staging\\\\n\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Single file ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/wordcount.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"print(r.stdout)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Multiple files ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/wordcount.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\", \\\"/tmp/notes.txt\\\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"print(r.stdout)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Error: no arguments ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/wordcount.py\\\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"stderr:\\\", r.stderr.strip())\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"exit code:\\\", r.returncode)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Error: file not found ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/wordcount.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/ghost.txt\\\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"stderr:\\\", r.stderr.strip())\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"exit code:\\\", r.returncode)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### Key `sys.argv` patterns to know\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Simulating sys.argv parsing patterns (safe to run in notebook)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def demo_argv_parsing(fake_argv):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Show common sys.argv access patterns.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"argv = {fake_argv}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # Script name\\n\",","    \"    script = fake_argv[0]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # Positional arguments (skip script name)\\n\",","    \"    args = fake_argv[1:]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # Boolean flags\\n\",","    \"    verbose = \\\"--verbose\\\" in args or \\\"-v\\\" in args\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # Value flags  (e.g. --output report.txt)\\n\",","    \"    output = None\\n\",","    \"    if \\\"--output\\\" in args:\\n\",","    \"        idx = args.index(\\\"--output\\\")\\n\",","    \"        output = args[idx + 1] if idx + 1 \u003c len(args) else None\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # Positional (non-flag) arguments\\n\",","    \"    positional = [a for a in args if not a.startswith(\\\"-\\\")]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  script:     {script}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  verbose:    {verbose}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  output:     {output}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  positional: {positional}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"demo_argv_parsing([\\\"myapp.py\\\", \\\"file1.txt\\\", \\\"file2.txt\\\", \\\"-v\\\"])\\n\",","    \"demo_argv_parsing([\\\"myapp.py\\\", \\\"data.csv\\\", \\\"--output\\\", \\\"report.txt\\\", \\\"--verbose\\\"])\\n\",","    \"demo_argv_parsing([\\\"myapp.py\\\"])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"💡 Tip: sys.argv works but gets messy fast.\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"   For anything beyond 2-3 simple args → use argparse (Section 3).\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 2\\n\",","    \"Write a `csvinfo.py` script using only `sys.argv` that:\\n\",","    \"- Takes one positional argument: a CSV filename\\n\",","    \"- Prints the number of rows, number of columns, and column names\\n\",","    \"- Handles missing file argument and file-not-found errors with useful messages and exit code 1\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import csv, subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Create a sample CSV to test against\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/sales.csv\\\", \\\"w\\\", newline=\\\"\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    writer = csv.writer(f)\\n\",","    \"    writer.writerow([\\\"date\\\", \\\"product\\\", \\\"quantity\\\", \\\"revenue\\\"])\\n\",","    \"    writer.writerows([\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"2024-01-15\\\", \\\"Headphones\\\", 3, 389.97],\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"2024-01-16\\\", \\\"Keyboard\\\",   1,  89.99],\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"2024-01-17\\\", \\\"Mouse\\\",      2,  69.98],\\n\",","    \"    ])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import sys, csv, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def csv_info(path):\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/csvinfo.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Test:\\n\",","    \"# r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/csvinfo.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/sales.csv\\\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"# print(r.stdout)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 3 — `argparse`: Professional Argument Parsing\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"`argparse` is Python's built-in argument parser. It gives you:\\n\",","    \"- Automatic `--help` generation\\n\",","    \"- Type validation (`int`, `float`, `Path`)\\n\",","    \"- Required vs. optional arguments\\n\",","    \"- Choices, defaults, and mutually exclusive groups\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 🔍 Scenario: Server log file analyser\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Generate sample log file ─────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"log_lines = [\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:12:34 INFO  [auth]    User alice logged in',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:13:01 INFO  [api]     GET /products 200 45ms',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:14:22 WARN  [api]     GET /orders 429 rate limited',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:15:07 ERROR [db]      Connection timeout after 30s',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:16:44 INFO  [api]     POST /checkout 200 112ms',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:17:15 ERROR [api]     POST /payment 500 internal error',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:18:33 INFO  [auth]    User bob logged in',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:19:02 WARN  [cache]   Cache miss rate above 40%',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:20:11 ERROR [db]      Deadlock detected on orders table',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:21:00 INFO  [api]     GET /health 200 3ms',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:22:45 ERROR [auth]    Failed login attempt for root',\\n\",","    \"    '2024-06-01 08:23:18 INFO  [api]     DELETE /session 200 8ms',\\n\",","    \"]\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(\\\"\\\\n\\\".join(log_lines))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── The CLI script ───────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"loganalyser = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    import argparse\\n\",","    \"    import sys\\n\",","    \"    from collections import Counter\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def parse_log(path, level=None, component=None, tail=None):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Read and filter log lines.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"            lines = f.readlines()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if tail:\\n\",","    \"            lines = lines[-tail:]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        results = []\\n\",","    \"        for line in lines:\\n\",","    \"            parts = line.split()\\n\",","    \"            if len(parts) \u003c 4:\\n\",","    \"                continue\\n\",","    \"            log_level = parts[2]\\n\",","    \"            log_comp  = parts[3].strip(\\\"[]\\\")\\n\",","    \"            if level and log_level != level.upper():\\n\",","    \"                continue\\n\",","    \"            if component and log_comp != component:\\n\",","    \"                continue\\n\",","    \"            results.append(line.rstrip())\\n\",","    \"        return results\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def summarise(path):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Print a summary of log levels.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"            lines = f.readlines()\\n\",","    \"        counts = Counter()\\n\",","    \"        for line in lines:\\n\",","    \"            parts = line.split()\\n\",","    \"            if len(parts) \u003e= 3:\\n\",","    \"                counts[parts[2]] += 1\\n\",","    \"        total = sum(counts.values())\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Log summary for: {path}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Total entries:   {total}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        for lvl in [\\\"INFO\\\", \\\"WARN\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\"]:\\n\",","    \"            n = counts.get(lvl, 0)\\n\",","    \"            bar = \\\"#\\\" * n\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {lvl:\u003c6} {n:\u003e4}  {bar}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"            prog=\\\"loganalyser\\\",\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"Analyse server log files.\\\",\\n\",","    \"            epilog=\\\"Example: loganalyser server.log --level ERROR --component db\\\"\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Positional: required\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"logfile\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Path to the log file\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Optional with choices\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--level\\\", \\\"-l\\\",\\n\",","    \"            choices=[\\\"INFO\\\", \\\"WARN\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\"],\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Filter by log level\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Optional string\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--component\\\", \\\"-c\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Filter by component (e.g. db, api, auth)\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Optional int with default\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--tail\\\", \\\"-n\\\",\\n\",","    \"            type=int,\\n\",","    \"            metavar=\\\"N\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Only show last N lines\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Boolean flag\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--summary\\\", \\\"-s\\\",\\n\",","    \"            action=\\\"store_true\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Print a level summary instead of lines\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Output file (optional)\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--output\\\", \\\"-o\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Write results to this file instead of stdout\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return parser\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = build_parser()\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if args.summary:\\n\",","    \"            summarise(args.logfile)\\n\",","    \"            return\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        lines = parse_log(args.logfile, args.level, args.component, args.tail)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        out = open(args.output, \\\"w\\\") if args.output else sys.stdout\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            if not lines:\\n\",","    \"                print(\\\"No matching log entries.\\\", file=out)\\n\",","    \"            else:\\n\",","    \"                for line in lines:\\n\",","    \"                    print(line, file=out)\\n\",","    \"                if args.output:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"Wrote {len(lines)} lines to {args.output}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"        finally:\\n\",","    \"            if args.output:\\n\",","    \"                out.close()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/loganalyser.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(loganalyser)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def run(args, label):\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/loganalyser.py\\\"] + args,\\n\",","    \"                       capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n$ loganalyser {' '.join(args)}   [{label}]\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(r.stdout or r.stderr)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"run([\\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"--summary\\\"], \\\"summary\\\")\\n\",","    \"run([\\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"--level\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\"], \\\"errors only\\\")\\n\",","    \"run([\\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"--level\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\", \\\"--component\\\", \\\"db\\\"], \\\"db errors\\\")\\n\",","    \"run([\\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"--tail\\\", \\\"4\\\"], \\\"last 4 lines\\\")\\n\",","    \"run([\\\"/tmp/loganalyser.py\\\", \\\"--help\\\"], \\\"help text\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### `argparse` argument types quick-reference\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import argparse\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Creating a parser and demonstrating all key argument types\\n\",","    \"# (We'll use parse_known_args so this is safe inside a notebook)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\\\"argparse feature demo\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 1. Positional argument (required, no --flag needed)\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"filename\\\",\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"Input file to process\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 2. Optional argument with type coercion\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"--count\\\", type=int, default=10,\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"Number of results (default: 10)\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 3. Boolean flag (store_true / store_false)\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"--verbose\\\", \\\"-v\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\",\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"Enable verbose output\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 4. Constrained choices\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"--format\\\", choices=[\\\"csv\\\", \\\"json\\\", \\\"table\\\"], default=\\\"table\\\",\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"Output format\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 5. Multiple values  (nargs)\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"--tags\\\", nargs=\\\"+\\\",\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"One or more tags (e.g. --tags urgent billing)\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 6. Append multiple uses of the same flag\\n\",","    \"parser.add_argument(\\\"--exclude\\\", action=\\\"append\\\",\\n\",","    \"    help=\\\"Exclude a pattern (repeatable: --exclude a --exclude b)\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Simulate parsing various argument strings ────────────────\\n\",","    \"test_cases = [\\n\",","    \"    \\\"data.csv\\\",\\n\",","    \"    \\\"data.csv --count 5 --verbose\\\",\\n\",","    \"    \\\"data.csv --format json --tags urgent billing --exclude tmp\\\",\\n\",","    \"    \\\"data.csv --exclude a --exclude b --exclude c\\\",\\n\",","    \"]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"for cmd in test_cases:\\n\",","    \"    args, _ = parser.parse_known_args(cmd.split())\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"Input: {cmd}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  filename={args.filename}, count={args.count}, verbose={args.verbose}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  format={args.format}, tags={args.tags}, exclude={args.exclude}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print()\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 3\\n\",","    \"Build a `csv_filter.py` CLI with `argparse` that:\\n\",","    \"- Takes a CSV file as a positional argument\\n\",","    \"- `--column` (required): column name to filter on\\n\",","    \"- `--value` (required): value to match\\n\",","    \"- `--output` (optional): write results to file instead of stdout\\n\",","    \"- `--count` flag: just print the number of matching rows instead of the rows themselves\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, csv, sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def filter_csv(path, column, value):\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/csv_filter.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Test:\\n\",","    \"# r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/csv_filter.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/sales.csv\\\",\\n\",","    \"#                     \\\"--column\\\", \\\"product\\\", \\\"--value\\\", \\\"Headphones\\\"],\\n\",","    \"#                    capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"# print(r.stdout)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 4 — Subcommands (Git-Style CLI)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Many professional tools expose multiple commands under one program:\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"git  commit  -m \\\"message\\\"\\n\",","    \"git  push    origin main\\n\",","    \"aws  s3      cp file.txt s3://bucket/\\n\",","    \"docker build -t myapp .\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"`argparse` supports this with `add_subparsers()`.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📁 Scenario: A project manager CLI (`proj`)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap, json, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"proj_script = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    #!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    proj — a simple project task manager\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    Usage:\\n\",","    \"      proj add \\\"Task name\\\" [--priority high|medium|low]\\n\",","    \"      proj list [--status open|done] [--priority high]\\n\",","    \"      proj done \u003ctask_id\u003e\\n\",","    \"      proj delete \u003ctask_id\u003e\\n\",","    \"      proj stats\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, json, sys, os\\n\",","    \"    from datetime import datetime\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    DB_FILE = \\\"/tmp/proj_tasks.json\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ── Data layer ──────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    def load_tasks():\\n\",","    \"        if not os.path.exists(DB_FILE):\\n\",","    \"            return []\\n\",","    \"        with open(DB_FILE) as f:\\n\",","    \"            return json.load(f)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def save_tasks(tasks):\\n\",","    \"        with open(DB_FILE, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"            json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def next_id(tasks):\\n\",","    \"        return max((t[\\\"id\\\"] for t in tasks), default=0) + 1\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ── Command handlers ─────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_add(args):\\n\",","    \"        tasks = load_tasks()\\n\",","    \"        task = {\\n\",","    \"            \\\"id\\\": next_id(tasks),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"title\\\": args.title,\\n\",","    \"            \\\"priority\\\": args.priority,\\n\",","    \"            \\\"status\\\": \\\"open\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"created\\\": datetime.now().strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\\\")\\n\",","    \"        }\\n\",","    \"        tasks.append(task)\\n\",","    \"        save_tasks(tasks)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Added task #{task[\\\\'id\\\\']}: {task[\\\\'title\\\\']} [{task[\\\\'priority\\\\']}]\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_list(args):\\n\",","    \"        tasks = load_tasks()\\n\",","    \"        filtered = [\\n\",","    \"            t for t in tasks\\n\",","    \"            if (not args.status   or t[\\\"status\\\"]   == args.status)\\n\",","    \"            and (not args.priority or t[\\\"priority\\\"] == args.priority)\\n\",","    \"        ]\\n\",","    \"        if not filtered:\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"No matching tasks.\\\")\\n\",","    \"            return\\n\",","    \"        PRIORITY_ICON = {\\\"high\\\": \\\"🔴\\\", \\\"medium\\\": \\\"🟡\\\", \\\"low\\\": \\\"🟢\\\"}\\n\",","    \"        STATUS_ICON   = {\\\"open\\\": \\\"[ ]\\\", \\\"done\\\": \\\"[x]\\\"}\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  {'ID':\u003c4} {'Status':\u003c5} {'P':\u003c4} {'Title'}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"  \\\" + \\\"-\\\"*50)\\n\",","    \"        for t in filtered:\\n\",","    \"            icon = PRIORITY_ICON.get(t[\\\\'priority\\\\'], \\\" \\\")\\n\",","    \"            st   = STATUS_ICON.get(t[\\\\'status\\\\'], \\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {t[\\\\'id\\\\']:\u003c4} {st:\u003c5} {icon} {t[\\\\'title\\\\']}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_done(args):\\n\",","    \"        tasks = load_tasks()\\n\",","    \"        for t in tasks:\\n\",","    \"            if t[\\\"id\\\"] == args.task_id:\\n\",","    \"                t[\\\"status\\\"] = \\\"done\\\"\\n\",","    \"                save_tasks(tasks)\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"Marked task #{args.task_id} as done: {t[\\\\'title\\\\']}\\\")  \\n\",","    \"                return\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Task #{args.task_id} not found.\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"        sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_delete(args):\\n\",","    \"        tasks = load_tasks()\\n\",","    \"        original = len(tasks)\\n\",","    \"        tasks = [t for t in tasks if t[\\\"id\\\"] != args.task_id]\\n\",","    \"        if len(tasks) == original:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Task #{args.task_id} not found.\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        save_tasks(tasks)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Deleted task #{args.task_id}.\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_stats(args):\\n\",","    \"        tasks = load_tasks()\\n\",","    \"        total = len(tasks)\\n\",","    \"        done  = sum(1 for t in tasks if t[\\\"status\\\"] == \\\"done\\\")\\n\",","    \"        open_ = total - done\\n\",","    \"        by_priority = {\\\"high\\\": 0, \\\"medium\\\": 0, \\\"low\\\": 0}\\n\",","    \"        for t in tasks:\\n\",","    \"            by_priority[t[\\\"priority\\\"]] += 1\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Tasks: {total} total  |  {open_} open  |  {done} done\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Priority: high={by_priority[\\\\'high\\\\']}  medium={by_priority[\\\\'medium\\\\']}  low={by_priority[\\\\'low\\\\']}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ── Argument parser ──────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"            prog=\\\"proj\\\",\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"Simple project task manager\\\"\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"        subs = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"command\\\", metavar=\\\"COMMAND\\\")\\n\",","    \"        subs.required = True\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # add\\n\",","    \"        p_add = subs.add_parser(\\\"add\\\", help=\\\"Add a new task\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_add.add_argument(\\\"title\\\", help=\\\"Task title\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_add.add_argument(\\\"--priority\\\", \\\"-p\\\",\\n\",","    \"            choices=[\\\"high\\\", \\\"medium\\\", \\\"low\\\"], default=\\\"medium\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_add.set_defaults(func=cmd_add)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # list\\n\",","    \"        p_list = subs.add_parser(\\\"list\\\", help=\\\"List tasks\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_list.add_argument(\\\"--status\\\",   choices=[\\\"open\\\", \\\"done\\\"])\\n\",","    \"        p_list.add_argument(\\\"--priority\\\", choices=[\\\"high\\\", \\\"medium\\\", \\\"low\\\"])\\n\",","    \"        p_list.set_defaults(func=cmd_list)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # done\\n\",","    \"        p_done = subs.add_parser(\\\"done\\\", help=\\\"Mark a task complete\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_done.add_argument(\\\"task_id\\\", type=int)\\n\",","    \"        p_done.set_defaults(func=cmd_done)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # delete\\n\",","    \"        p_del = subs.add_parser(\\\"delete\\\", help=\\\"Delete a task\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_del.add_argument(\\\"task_id\\\", type=int)\\n\",","    \"        p_del.set_defaults(func=cmd_delete)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # stats\\n\",","    \"        p_stats = subs.add_parser(\\\"stats\\\", help=\\\"Show task statistics\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_stats.set_defaults(func=cmd_stats)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return parser\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = build_parser()\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"        args.func(args)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/proj.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(proj_script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Clear any old state\\n\",","    \"if os.path.exists(\\\"/tmp/proj_tasks.json\\\"):\\n\",","    \"    os.remove(\\\"/tmp/proj_tasks.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def proj(*args):\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/proj.py\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"                       capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"    output = (r.stdout + r.stderr).strip()\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"$ proj {' '.join(args)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  {output}\\\\n\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"add\\\", \\\"Fix login bug\\\", \\\"--priority\\\", \\\"high\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"add\\\", \\\"Write unit tests\\\", \\\"--priority\\\", \\\"medium\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"add\\\", \\\"Update README\\\", \\\"--priority\\\", \\\"low\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"add\\\", \\\"Deploy to staging\\\", \\\"--priority\\\", \\\"high\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"list\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"done\\\", \\\"1\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"list\\\", \\\"--status\\\", \\\"open\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"list\\\", \\\"--priority\\\", \\\"high\\\")\\n\",","    \"proj(\\\"stats\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 4\\n\",","    \"Add a `search` subcommand to `proj` that takes a `keyword` and prints all tasks whose title contains that keyword (case-insensitive).\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Hint: you need to:\\n\",","    \"# 1. Write a cmd_search(args) handler function\\n\",","    \"# 2. Add a \\\"search\\\" subparser to build_parser() with a \\\"keyword\\\" positional arg\\n\",","    \"# 3. Register cmd_search as its default func\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Your modified proj.py here — copy, edit, save to /tmp/proj2.py, test\\n\",","    \"# proj2(\\\"search\\\", \\\"bug\\\")\\n\",","    \"# proj2(\\\"search\\\", \\\"deploy\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 5 — stdin / stdout / stderr: The Unix Pipeline\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"The Unix philosophy: programs should read from stdin, write to stdout, and report errors to stderr. This lets them be **chained** with pipes (`|`).\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"```bash\\n\",","    \"cat access.log | grep ERROR | python3 summarise.py --top 5 \u003e report.txt\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📊 Scenario: A text transformation pipeline tool\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Script that reads from stdin OR a file ───────────────────\\n\",","    \"pipeline_tool = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, sys\\n\",","    \"    from collections import Counter\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def process(lines, transform):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Apply a transform to each line.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        for line in lines:\\n\",","    \"            line = line.rstrip(\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\")\\n\",","    \"            if transform == \\\"upper\\\":     yield line.upper()\\n\",","    \"            elif transform == \\\"lower\\\":   yield line.lower()\\n\",","    \"            elif transform == \\\"reverse\\\": yield line[::-1]\\n\",","    \"            elif transform == \\\"length\\\":  yield f\\\"{len(line):\u003e4}  {line}\\\"\\n\",","    \"            elif transform == \\\"number\\\":\\n\",","    \"                process.counter = getattr(process, \\\"counter\\\", 0) + 1\\n\",","    \"                yield f\\\"{process.counter:\u003e4}  {line}\\\"\\n\",","    \"            else:                        yield line\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def word_freq(lines, top_n):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Count word frequencies.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        counts = Counter()\\n\",","    \"        for line in lines:\\n\",","    \"            for word in line.lower().split():\\n\",","    \"                word = word.strip(\\\".,!?;:'\\\\\\\"\\\").strip()\\n\",","    \"                if word:\\n\",","    \"                    counts[word] += 1\\n\",","    \"        for word, count in counts.most_common(top_n):\\n\",","    \"            yield f\\\"{count:\u003e6}  {word}\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"Text pipeline transformer. Reads from file or stdin.\\\"\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"file\\\", nargs=\\\"?\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Input file (omit to read from stdin)\\\")\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--transform\\\", \\\"-t\\\",\\n\",","    \"            choices=[\\\"upper\\\", \\\"lower\\\", \\\"reverse\\\", \\\"length\\\", \\\"number\\\"],\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Transform to apply to each line\\\")\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--freq\\\",\\n\",","    \"            action=\\\"store_true\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Count word frequencies instead\\\")\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--top\\\", type=int, default=10,\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Top N words to show (with --freq, default: 10)\\\")\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # ── Read from file or stdin ─────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"        if args.file:\\n\",","    \"            try:\\n\",","    \"                src = open(args.file)\\n\",","    \"            except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"Error: {args.file} not found\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"                sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            if sys.stdin.isatty():\\n\",","    \"                print(\\\"Reading from stdin (Ctrl+D to end)...\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            src = sys.stdin\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        lines = src.readlines()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # ── Write to stdout ─────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"        if args.freq:\\n\",","    \"            for line in word_freq(lines, args.top):\\n\",","    \"                print(line)\\n\",","    \"        elif args.transform:\\n\",","    \"            for line in process(lines, args.transform):\\n\",","    \"                print(line)\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            # Default: just echo with line numbers\\n\",","    \"            for i, line in enumerate(lines, 1):\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"{i:\u003e4}  {line.rstrip()}\\\")  \\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if args.file:\\n\",","    \"            src.close()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/txtool.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(pipeline_tool)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Sample text for testing\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/sample.txt\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(\\\"\\\"\\\"Python is a high-level programming language.\\n\",","    \"Python is used in data science, web development, and automation.\\n\",","    \"Many developers love Python for its readability.\\n\",","    \"The Python community is large and welcoming.\\n\",","    \"Learning Python opens many career opportunities.\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def txtool(*args, stdin_data=None):\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/txtool.py\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"        input=stdin_data, capture_output=True, text=True\\n\",","    \"    )\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"$ txtool {' '.join(args)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(r.stdout or r.stderr)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"txtool(\\\"/tmp/sample.txt\\\")                          # Line numbers\\n\",","    \"txtool(\\\"/tmp/sample.txt\\\", \\\"--transform\\\", \\\"upper\\\")  # Uppercase\\n\",","    \"txtool(\\\"/tmp/sample.txt\\\", \\\"--freq\\\", \\\"--top\\\", \\\"5\\\")  # Word frequency\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Pipe: echo | txtool (stdin mode)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"$ echo 'Hello World from Pipe' | txtool --transform upper\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/txtool.py\\\", \\\"--transform\\\", \\\"upper\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    input=\\\"Hello World from Pipe\\\\n\\\", capture_output=True, text=True\\n\",","    \")\\n\",","    \"print(r.stdout)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# stdin / stdout / stderr pattern reference\\n\",","    \"import sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== stdout vs stderr ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# stdout: normal output (goes to terminal or pipe)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"This is normal output\\\", file=sys.stdout)   # same as print()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# stderr: diagnostic/error messages (always goes to terminal, never into pipes)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"This is an error/warning\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Checking if stdin is a terminal or a pipe ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"if sys.stdin.isatty():\\n\",","    \"    print(\\\"stdin is a terminal — user is typing interactively\\\")\\n\",","    \"else:\\n\",","    \"    print(\\\"stdin is a pipe — reading programmatic input\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Writing to a file via stdout redirect ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"In a shell you would do:\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"  $ python3 myapp.py \u003e output.txt      # redirect stdout to file\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"  $ python3 myapp.py 2\u003e errors.txt     # redirect stderr to file\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"  $ python3 myapp.py \u003e out.txt 2\u003e\u00261    # both to same file\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"  $ python3 myapp.py | grep ERROR      # pipe stdout to grep\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 5\\n\",","    \"Write a `dedup.py` pipeline tool that:\\n\",","    \"- Reads lines from a file or stdin\\n\",","    \"- Removes duplicate lines (preserving order of first appearance)\\n\",","    \"- `--count` flag: prefix each unique line with how many times it appeared\\n\",","    \"- `--ignore-case` flag: treat lines as equal regardless of case\\n\",","    \"- Writes to stdout (pipeable)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"script = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"import argparse, sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def dedup(lines, ignore_case=False, count=False):\\n\",","    \"    # Your code here\\n\",","    \"    pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def main():\\n\",","    \"    # Your code here — build argparse, read input, call dedup, write output\\n\",","    \"    pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"    main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/dedup.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# test_input = \\\"apple\\\\nbanana\\\\nAPPLE\\\\napple\\\\norange\\\\nbanana\\\\n\\\"\\n\",","    \"# r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/dedup.py\\\"], input=test_input, capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"# print(r.stdout)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 6 — Exit Codes \u0026 Error Handling\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Exit codes let shell scripts and CI/CD pipelines know if your program succeeded:\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"| Code | Meaning | Convention |\\n\",","    \"|------|---------|------------|\\n\",","    \"| `0` | Success | Always |\\n\",","    \"| `1` | General error | Unix standard |\\n\",","    \"| `2` | Misuse of CLI (bad args) | `argparse` default |\\n\",","    \"| `3–125` | App-specific errors | Your choice |\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 🚀 Scenario: Deployment pre-flight health checker\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"healthcheck = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    #!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    healthcheck.py  —  Pre-deployment environment validator\\n\",","    \"    Exit 0: all checks passed\\n\",","    \"    Exit 1: one or more checks failed (do not deploy)\\n\",","    \"    Exit 2: configuration error\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, sys, os, shutil, json\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    CHECKS = {}\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def check(name):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Decorator to register a check function.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        def decorator(fn):\\n\",","    \"            CHECKS[name] = fn\\n\",","    \"            return fn\\n\",","    \"        return decorator\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ── Individual checks ────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    @check(\\\"python-version\\\")\\n\",","    \"    def check_python(args):\\n\",","    \"        major, minor = sys.version_info[:2]\\n\",","    \"        if (major, minor) \u003c (3, 8):\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Python {major}.{minor} \u003c 3.8 required\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return True, f\\\"Python {major}.{minor}\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    @check(\\\"env-vars\\\")\\n\",","    \"    def check_env(args):\\n\",","    \"        required = [\\\"APP_ENV\\\", \\\"DATABASE_URL\\\", \\\"SECRET_KEY\\\"]\\n\",","    \"        missing = [v for v in required if not os.getenv(v)]\\n\",","    \"        if missing:\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Missing env vars: {\\\\', \\\\'.join(missing)}\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return True, \\\"All required env vars set\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    @check(\\\"disk-space\\\")\\n\",","    \"    def check_disk(args):\\n\",","    \"        stat = os.statvfs(\\\"/\\\")\\n\",","    \"        free_gb = (stat.f_frsize * stat.f_bavail) / (1024 ** 3)\\n\",","    \"        if free_gb \u003c 1.0:\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Only {free_gb:.1f}GB free (need 1GB+)\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return True, f\\\"{free_gb:.1f}GB free\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    @check(\\\"required-tools\\\")\\n\",","    \"    def check_tools(args):\\n\",","    \"        tools = [\\\"git\\\", \\\"python3\\\", \\\"pip\\\"]\\n\",","    \"        missing = [t for t in tools if not shutil.which(t)]\\n\",","    \"        if missing:\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Missing tools: {\\\\', \\\\'.join(missing)}\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return True, \\\"All required tools found\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    @check(\\\"config-file\\\")\\n\",","    \"    def check_config(args):\\n\",","    \"        config_path = getattr(args, \\\"config\\\", \\\"config.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"        if not os.path.exists(config_path):\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Config not found: {config_path}\\\"\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            with open(config_path) as f:\\n\",","    \"                json.load(f)\\n\",","    \"            return True, f\\\"Config valid: {config_path}\\\"\\n\",","    \"        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\\n\",","    \"            return False, f\\\"Config JSON error: {e}\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ── Runner ───────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    def run_checks(checks_to_run, args, strict=False):\\n\",","    \"        passed, failed = [], []\\n\",","    \"        TICK, CROSS = \\\"✅\\\", \\\"❌\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\" 🚀 PRE-DEPLOYMENT HEALTH CHECK\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        for name in checks_to_run:\\n\",","    \"            fn = CHECKS.get(name)\\n\",","    \"            if fn is None:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"  ⚠️  Unknown check: {name}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"                continue\\n\",","    \"            try:\\n\",","    \"                ok, msg = fn(args)\\n\",","    \"            except Exception as e:\\n\",","    \"                ok, msg = False, f\\\"Exception: {e}\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"            icon = TICK if ok else CROSS\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {icon}  {name:\u003c22}  {msg}\\\")\\n\",","    \"            (passed if ok else failed).append(name)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"-\\\" * 50)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  {len(passed)} passed, {len(failed)} failed\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return len(failed) == 0\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"Pre-deployment environment checker\\\"\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--checks\\\",\\n\",","    \"            nargs=\\\"+\\\",\\n\",","    \"            default=list(CHECKS.keys()),\\n\",","    \"            metavar=\\\"CHECK\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=f\\\"Checks to run (default: all). Available: {\\\\', \\\\'.join(CHECKS)}\\\"\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--config\\\", default=\\\"config.json\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Path to config file (for config-file check)\\\")\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--strict\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Exit 1 on first failure\\\")\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        all_passed = run_checks(args.checks, args)\\n\",","    \"        sys.exit(0 if all_passed else 1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/healthcheck.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(healthcheck)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Create a valid config file\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/config.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    json_content = '{\\\"env\\\": \\\"staging\\\", \\\"debug\\\": false, \\\"db_pool\\\": 10}'\\n\",","    \"    f.write(json_content)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def healthcheck(*args, env=None):\\n\",","    \"    import os\\n\",","    \"    environment = os.environ.copy()\\n\",","    \"    if env:\\n\",","    \"        environment.update(env)\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/healthcheck.py\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"        capture_output=True, text=True, env=environment\\n\",","    \"    )\\n\",","    \"    print(r.stdout)\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"Exit code: {r.returncode}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Run checks (env vars missing) ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"healthcheck(\\\"--checks\\\", \\\"python-version\\\", \\\"disk-space\\\", \\\"required-tools\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"--config\\\", \\\"/tmp/config.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Run with env vars set ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"healthcheck(\\\"--checks\\\", \\\"python-version\\\", \\\"disk-space\\\", \\\"required-tools\\\",\\n\",","    \"            env={\\\"APP_ENV\\\": \\\"staging\\\", \\\"DATABASE_URL\\\": \\\"postgres://localhost/db\\\", \\\"SECRET_KEY\\\": \\\"abc123\\\"})\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Exit code patterns — reference\\n\",","    \"import sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== How to use sys.exit() ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"print()\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"sys.exit(0)            # success\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"sys.exit(1)            # generic failure\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"sys.exit(2)            # bad arguments (argparse does this automatically)\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"sys.exit('message')    # prints message to stderr, then exits with code 1\\\")\\n\",","    \"print()\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Using exit codes in shell scripts ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"print('''\\n\",","    \"#!/bin/bash\\n\",","    \"python3 healthcheck.py\\n\",","    \"if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\\n\",","    \"    echo \\\"Checks passed — deploying...\\\"\\n\",","    \"    ./deploy.sh\\n\",","    \"else\\n\",","    \"    echo \\\"Health checks FAILED — deployment aborted\\\"\\n\",","    \"    exit 1\\n\",","    \"fi\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Or more concisely with \u0026\u0026 ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"python3 healthcheck.py \u0026\u0026 ./deploy.sh\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### ✏️ Exercise 6\\n\",","    \"Write a `validate_json.py` CLI that:\\n\",","    \"- Takes one or more JSON file paths as arguments\\n\",","    \"- Reports `✅ valid` or `❌ invalid: \u003cerror\u003e` for each\\n\",","    \"- Exits 0 if ALL files are valid, exits 1 if ANY are invalid\\n\",","    \"- `--quiet` flag: suppress per-file output, just set exit code\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Create test files\\n\",","    \"import json, subprocess, textwrap\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/good.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    json.dump({\\\"name\\\": \\\"Alice\\\", \\\"age\\\": 30}, f)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/bad.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write('{\\\"name\\\": \\\"Bob\\\", \\\"age\\\":}')   # invalid JSON\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"script = textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, json, sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def validate_file(path):\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        # Your code here\\n\",","    \"        pass\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/validate_json.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/validate_json.py\\\", \\\"/tmp/good.json\\\", \\\"/tmp/bad.json\\\"],\\n\",","    \"#                    capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"# print(r.stdout)\\n\",","    \"# print(\\\"Exit code:\\\", r.returncode)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 7 — Config Files \u0026 Environment Variables\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Real CLI tools read configuration from multiple sources, in priority order:\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"Command-line flags  (highest priority — always wins)\\n\",","    \"    ↑\\n\",","    \"Environment variables\\n\",","    \"    ↑\\n\",","    \"Config file  (~/.myapp.cfg or ./myapp.yaml)\\n\",","    \"    ↑\\n\",","    \"Built-in defaults  (lowest priority)\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 🔑 Scenario: API key manager for a data pipeline tool\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import textwrap, subprocess, os, json\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"config_script = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    #!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    datapipe.py — Data pipeline tool with layered config\\n\",","    \"    Config resolution: CLI flags \u003e env vars \u003e config file \u003e defaults\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, os, sys, json\\n\",","    \"    from pathlib import Path\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    CONFIG_FILE = Path.home() / \\\".datapipe.json\\\"\\n\",","    \"    DEFAULTS = {\\n\",","    \"        \\\"api_url\\\":    \\\"https://api.example.com\\\",\\n\",","    \"        \\\"timeout\\\":    30,\\n\",","    \"        \\\"max_retries\\\": 3,\\n\",","    \"        \\\"output_dir\\\": \\\"./output\\\",\\n\",","    \"        \\\"log_level\\\":  \\\"INFO\\\",\\n\",","    \"    }\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def load_config_file(path):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Load config from JSON file, return {} if not found.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        if path.exists():\\n\",","    \"            try:\\n\",","    \"                with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"                    return json.load(f)\\n\",","    \"            except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"Warning: invalid config file {path}: {e}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"        return {}\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def save_config_file(path, config):\\n\",","    \"        with open(path, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"            json.dump(config, f, indent=2)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Config saved to {path}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def resolve_config(args):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Merge config from all sources. CLI \u003e env \u003e file \u003e defaults.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        # Layer 1: defaults\\n\",","    \"        config = dict(DEFAULTS)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Layer 2: config file\\n\",","    \"        file_config = load_config_file(CONFIG_FILE)\\n\",","    \"        config.update(file_config)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Layer 3: environment variables\\n\",","    \"        env_mapping = {\\n\",","    \"            \\\"DATAPIPE_API_URL\\\":     \\\"api_url\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"DATAPIPE_API_KEY\\\":     \\\"api_key\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"DATAPIPE_TIMEOUT\\\":     \\\"timeout\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"DATAPIPE_OUTPUT_DIR\\\":  \\\"output_dir\\\",\\n\",","    \"            \\\"DATAPIPE_LOG_LEVEL\\\":   \\\"log_level\\\",\\n\",","    \"        }\\n\",","    \"        for env_var, key in env_mapping.items():\\n\",","    \"            val = os.getenv(env_var)\\n\",","    \"            if val is not None:\\n\",","    \"                config[key] = val\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # Layer 4: CLI flags (override everything)\\n\",","    \"        if getattr(args, \\\"api_url\\\", None):    config[\\\"api_url\\\"]    = args.api_url\\n\",","    \"        if getattr(args, \\\"api_key\\\", None):    config[\\\"api_key\\\"]    = args.api_key\\n\",","    \"        if getattr(args, \\\"timeout\\\", None):    config[\\\"timeout\\\"]    = args.timeout\\n\",","    \"        if getattr(args, \\\"output_dir\\\", None): config[\\\"output_dir\\\"] = args.output_dir\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return config\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def mask(value):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Mask sensitive values for display.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        if not value:\\n\",","    \"            return \\\"(not set)\\\"\\n\",","    \"        s = str(value)\\n\",","    \"        return s[:4] + \\\"****\\\" if len(s) \u003e 4 else \\\"****\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_config_show(args):\\n\",","    \"        cfg = resolve_config(args)\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"Current configuration (resolved from all sources):\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print()\\n\",","    \"        for key, val in cfg.items():\\n\",","    \"            display = mask(val) if key in (\\\"api_key\\\", \\\"secret\\\") else val\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {key:\u003c16}  {display}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_config_set(args):\\n\",","    \"        file_config = load_config_file(CONFIG_FILE)\\n\",","    \"        file_config[args.key] = args.value\\n\",","    \"        save_config_file(CONFIG_FILE, file_config)\\n\",","    \"        masked = mask(args.value) if args.key in (\\\"api_key\\\", \\\"secret\\\") else args.value\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Set {args.key} = {masked}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_config_unset(args):\\n\",","    \"        file_config = load_config_file(CONFIG_FILE)\\n\",","    \"        if args.key in file_config:\\n\",","    \"            del file_config[args.key]\\n\",","    \"            save_config_file(CONFIG_FILE, file_config)\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Removed {args.key} from config.\\\")\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"{args.key} was not set in config file.\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_run(args):\\n\",","    \"        cfg = resolve_config(args)\\n\",","    \"        if not cfg.get(\\\"api_key\\\"):\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"Error: api_key not configured.\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"  Set via: datapipe config set api_key YOUR_KEY\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"       or: export DATAPIPE_API_KEY=YOUR_KEY\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"Running pipeline against {cfg[\\\\'api_url\\\\']}...\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  Timeout: {cfg[\\\\'timeout\\\\']}s | Retries: {cfg[\\\\'max_retries\\\\']} | Output: {cfg[\\\\'output_dir\\\\']}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(\\\"  [simulation] Pipeline complete.\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(prog=\\\"datapipe\\\",\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"Data pipeline tool\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        subs = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"command\\\")\\n\",","    \"        subs.required = True\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # run\\n\",","    \"        p_run = subs.add_parser(\\\"run\\\", help=\\\"Run the pipeline\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_run.add_argument(\\\"--api-url\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_run.add_argument(\\\"--api-key\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_run.add_argument(\\\"--timeout\\\", type=int)\\n\",","    \"        p_run.add_argument(\\\"--output-dir\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_run.set_defaults(func=cmd_run)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # config\\n\",","    \"        p_cfg = subs.add_parser(\\\"config\\\", help=\\\"Manage configuration\\\")\\n\",","    \"        cfg_subs = p_cfg.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"config_cmd\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_show = cfg_subs.add_parser(\\\"show\\\", help=\\\"Show resolved config\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_show.set_defaults(func=cmd_config_show)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_set = cfg_subs.add_parser(\\\"set\\\", help=\\\"Set a config value\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_set.add_argument(\\\"key\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_set.add_argument(\\\"value\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_set.set_defaults(func=cmd_config_set)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_unset = cfg_subs.add_parser(\\\"unset\\\", help=\\\"Remove a config value\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_unset.add_argument(\\\"key\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_unset.set_defaults(func=cmd_config_unset)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return parser\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = build_parser()\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"        args.func(args)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/datapipe.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(config_script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Clear any prior config file\\n\",","    \"home_cfg = os.path.expanduser(\\\"~/.datapipe.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"if os.path.exists(home_cfg):\\n\",","    \"    os.remove(home_cfg)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def datapipe(*args, env=None):\\n\",","    \"    environment = os.environ.copy()\\n\",","    \"    # Remove any leftover vars\\n\",","    \"    for k in [\\\"DATAPIPE_API_URL\\\",\\\"DATAPIPE_API_KEY\\\",\\\"DATAPIPE_TIMEOUT\\\",\\\"DATAPIPE_OUTPUT_DIR\\\"]:\\n\",","    \"        environment.pop(k, None)\\n\",","    \"    if env:\\n\",","    \"        environment.update(env)\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/datapipe.py\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"        capture_output=True, text=True, env=environment\\n\",","    \"    )\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"$ datapipe {' '.join(args)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(r.stdout or r.stderr)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"config\\\", \\\"show\\\")\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"config\\\", \\\"set\\\", \\\"api_key\\\", \\\"sk-prod-abc123xyz\\\")\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"config\\\", \\\"set\\\", \\\"output_dir\\\", \\\"/data/pipeline-results\\\")\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"config\\\", \\\"show\\\")\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"run\\\")\\n\",","    \"datapipe(\\\"run\\\", env={\\\"DATAPIPE_API_URL\\\": \\\"https://staging.api.example.com\\\"})\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 8 — Progress Bars \u0026 Rich Terminal Output\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Good CLI UX means giving users feedback for long-running operations.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📂 Scenario: Bulk file processor with progress reporting\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import sys, time, os, shutil\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── A progress bar using only the standard library ──────────\\n\",","    \"def progress_bar(current, total, label=\\\"\\\", width=40):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    Print an in-place progress bar to stderr.\\n\",","    \"    Uses carriage return (\\\\\\\\r) to overwrite the same line.\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    pct   = current / total if total else 0\\n\",","    \"    filled = int(width * pct)\\n\",","    \"    bar   = \\\"█\\\" * filled + \\\"░\\\" * (width - filled)\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\r  [{bar}] {pct*100:5.1f}%  {current}/{total}  {label:\u003c30}\\\",\\n\",","    \"          end=\\\"\\\", flush=True, file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"    if current == total:\\n\",","    \"        print(file=sys.stderr)  # newline at completion\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def spinner(message, done=False):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Simple spinner for indeterminate waits.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    chars = \\\"|/-\\\\\\\\\\\"\\n\",","    \"    if done:\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"\\\\r  ✅ {message}\\\" + \\\" \\\" * 20, file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"    else:\\n\",","    \"        # In a real app you'd rotate; here we just show all frames for demo\\n\",","    \"        for c in chars:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"\\\\r  {c} {message}\\\", end=\\\"\\\", flush=True, file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            time.sleep(0.05)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Simulate bulk file processing ───────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"def process_files_demo(n_files=15):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Simulate processing N files with a progress bar.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"Processing {n_files} files...\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"    results = {\\\"ok\\\": 0, \\\"skip\\\": 0, \\\"error\\\": 0}\\n\",","    \"    \\n\",","    \"    for i in range(1, n_files + 1):\\n\",","    \"        # Simulate work\\n\",","    \"        time.sleep(0.03)\\n\",","    \"        \\n\",","    \"        # Simulate occasional errors and skips\\n\",","    \"        if i % 7 == 0:\\n\",","    \"            results[\\\"error\\\"] += 1\\n\",","    \"            status = f\\\"file_{i:02d}.csv ❌\\\"\\n\",","    \"        elif i % 5 == 0:\\n\",","    \"            results[\\\"skip\\\"] += 1\\n\",","    \"            status = f\\\"file_{i:02d}.csv ⏭️\\\"\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            results[\\\"ok\\\"] += 1\\n\",","    \"            status = f\\\"file_{i:02d}.csv ✅\\\"\\n\",","    \"        \\n\",","    \"        progress_bar(i, n_files, label=status)\\n\",","    \"    \\n\",","    \"    return results\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"results = process_files_demo(20)\\n\",","    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n  Summary: {results['ok']} processed, {results['skip']} skipped, {results['error']} errors\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# ── Colour output using ANSI escape codes (no dependencies) ──\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"class Color:\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"ANSI colour codes for terminal output.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    RESET   = \\\"\\\\033[0m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    BOLD    = \\\"\\\\033[1m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    RED     = \\\"\\\\033[91m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    GREEN   = \\\"\\\\033[92m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    YELLOW  = \\\"\\\\033[93m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    BLUE    = \\\"\\\\033[94m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    MAGENTA = \\\"\\\\033[95m\\\"\\n\",","    \"    CYAN    = \\\"\\\\033[96m\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    @classmethod\\n\",","    \"    def enabled(cls):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return False if not a real terminal (e.g. piped output).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return sys.stdout.isatty()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def colorize(text, color, bold=False):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Wrap text in ANSI codes only when outputting to a real terminal.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    if not sys.stdout.isatty():   # Plain text for pipes / file redirects\\n\",","    \"        return text\\n\",","    \"    prefix = (Color.BOLD if bold else \\\"\\\") + color\\n\",","    \"    return f\\\"{prefix}{text}{Color.RESET}\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def log(level, message):\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Structured log-like output with colour levels.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    colours = {\\n\",","    \"        \\\"INFO\\\":  Color.CYAN,\\n\",","    \"        \\\"OK\\\":    Color.GREEN,\\n\",","    \"        \\\"WARN\\\":  Color.YELLOW,\\n\",","    \"        \\\"ERROR\\\": Color.RED,\\n\",","    \"    }\\n\",","    \"    colour   = colours.get(level, Color.RESET)\\n\",","    \"    label    = colorize(f\\\"[{level}]\\\", colour, bold=True)\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  {label:\u003c10} {message}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Demo\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Coloured CLI Output ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"log(\\\"INFO\\\",  \\\"Starting deployment pipeline\\\")\\n\",","    \"log(\\\"OK\\\",    \\\"Database migrations complete\\\")\\n\",","    \"log(\\\"OK\\\",    \\\"Static assets uploaded\\\")\\n\",","    \"log(\\\"WARN\\\",  \\\"Memory usage at 78% — consider scaling\\\")\\n\",","    \"log(\\\"ERROR\\\", \\\"Health check failed for instance i-0a1b2c3d\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Table formatting\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Formatted Table (no dependencies) ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def print_table(headers, rows):\\n\",","    \"    widths = [max(len(str(r[i])) for r in [headers] + rows) for i in range(len(headers))]\\n\",","    \"    def row_str(row):\\n\",","    \"        return \\\"  \\\" + \\\"  \\\".join(str(v).ljust(widths[i]) for i, v in enumerate(row))\\n\",","    \"    print(row_str(headers))\\n\",","    \"    print(\\\"  \\\" + \\\"  \\\".join(\\\"-\\\" * w for w in widths))\\n\",","    \"    for row in rows:\\n\",","    \"        print(row_str(row))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print_table(\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"Service\\\",     \\\"Status\\\", \\\"CPU%\\\", \\\"Mem%\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    [\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"web-api\\\",     \\\"🟢 UP\\\",  \\\"12\\\",  \\\"34\\\"],\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"worker\\\",      \\\"🟢 UP\\\",  \\\"45\\\",  \\\"67\\\"],\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"scheduler\\\",   \\\"🔴 DOWN\\\",\\\"0\\\",   \\\"0\\\" ],\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"cache\\\",       \\\"🟡 SLOW\\\",\\\"8\\\",   \\\"91\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    ]\\n\",","    \")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 9 — Packaging \u0026 Entry Points\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"To make your CLI **installable** (`pip install myapp` → `myapp` command), you need a `setup.py` or `pyproject.toml`.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📦 Project structure for a deployable CLI\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, textwrap, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Build a minimal installable package ──────────────────────\\n\",","    \"PKG = \\\"/tmp/mygrep_pkg\\\"\\n\",","    \"os.makedirs(f\\\"{PKG}/mygrep\\\", exist_ok=True)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 1. The package code\\n\",","    \"with open(f\\\"{PKG}/mygrep/__init__.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write('__version__ = \\\"1.0.0\\\"\\\\n')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(f\\\"{PKG}/mygrep/core.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        def search_lines(lines, pattern, ignore_case=False, invert=False):\\n\",","    \"            \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Core search logic — pure, no I/O, fully testable.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\n\",","    \"            import re\\n\",","    \"            flags = re.IGNORECASE if ignore_case else 0\\n\",","    \"            results = []\\n\",","    \"            for i, line in enumerate(lines, start=1):\\n\",","    \"                match = bool(re.search(pattern, line, flags))\\n\",","    \"                if match != invert:\\n\",","    \"                    results.append((i, line.rstrip()))\\n\",","    \"            return results\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(f\\\"{PKG}/mygrep/cli.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        import argparse, sys\\n\",","    \"        from mygrep.core import search_lines\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"            p = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"                prog=\\\"mygrep\\\",\\n\",","    \"                description=\\\"Search files for a pattern (like grep, but Python).\\\"\\n\",","    \"            )\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"pattern\\\", help=\\\"Regex pattern to search for\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"files\\\", nargs=\\\"*\\\", help=\\\"Files to search (omit for stdin)\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"-i\\\", \\\"--ignore-case\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"-v\\\", \\\"--invert\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\", help=\\\"Invert match\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"-n\\\", \\\"--line-numbers\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"-c\\\", \\\"--count\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\", help=\\\"Only print count\\\")\\n\",","    \"            p.add_argument(\\\"--version\\\", action=\\\"version\\\", version=\\\"mygrep 1.0.0\\\")\\n\",","    \"            return p\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        def main():\\n\",","    \"            args = build_parser().parse_args()\\n\",","    \"            sources = []\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"            if args.files:\\n\",","    \"                for path in args.files:\\n\",","    \"                    try:\\n\",","    \"                        with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"                            sources.append((path, f.readlines()))\\n\",","    \"                    except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"                        print(f\\\"mygrep: {path}: No such file\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            else:\\n\",","    \"                sources.append((\\\"\u003cstdin\u003e\\\", sys.stdin.readlines()))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"            total_matches = 0\\n\",","    \"            for name, lines in sources:\\n\",","    \"                matches = search_lines(lines, args.pattern, args.ignore_case, args.invert)\\n\",","    \"                total_matches += len(matches)\\n\",","    \"                prefix = f\\\"{name}:\\\" if len(sources) \u003e 1 else \\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"                if args.count:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"{prefix}{len(matches)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"                else:\\n\",","    \"                    for lineno, line in matches:\\n\",","    \"                        num = f\\\"{lineno}:\\\" if args.line_numbers else \\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"                        print(f\\\"{prefix}{num}{line}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(0 if total_matches \u003e 0 else 1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"            main()\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 2. setup.py  (the entry point magic lives here)\\n\",","    \"with open(f\\\"{PKG}/setup.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        from setuptools import setup, find_packages\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        setup(\\n\",","    \"            name=\\\"mygrep\\\",\\n\",","    \"            version=\\\"1.0.0\\\",\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"A simple grep-like CLI tool\\\",\\n\",","    \"            packages=find_packages(),\\n\",","    \"            python_requires=\\\"\u003e=3.8\\\",\\n\",","    \"            entry_points={\\n\",","    \"                \\\"console_scripts\\\": [\\n\",","    \"                    # FORMAT:  \\\"command-name = package.module:function\\\"\\n\",","    \"                    \\\"mygrep = mygrep.cli:main\\\",\\n\",","    \"                ],\\n\",","    \"            },\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 3. Optional: pyproject.toml (modern alternative to setup.py)\\n\",","    \"with open(f\\\"{PKG}/pyproject.toml\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(textwrap.dedent(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        [build-system]\\n\",","    \"        requires = [\\\"setuptools\u003e=65\\\", \\\"wheel\\\"]\\n\",","    \"        build-backend = \\\"setuptools.backends.legacy:build\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        [project]\\n\",","    \"        name = \\\"mygrep\\\"\\n\",","    \"        version = \\\"1.0.0\\\"\\n\",","    \"        description = \\\"A simple grep-like CLI tool\\\"\\n\",","    \"        requires-python = \\\"\u003e=3.8\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        [project.scripts]\\n\",","    \"        mygrep = \\\"mygrep.cli:main\\\"\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# 4. Install in editable mode\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"Installing mygrep...\\\")\\n\",","    \"r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-e\\\", PKG, \\\"--quiet\\\", \\\"--break-system-packages\\\"],\\n\",","    \"    capture_output=True, text=True\\n\",","    \")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"Install output:\\\", r.stdout.strip() or \\\"(no output)\\\")\\n\",","    \"if r.returncode != 0:\\n\",","    \"    print(\\\"Error:\\\", r.stderr[:200])\\n\",","    \"else:\\n\",","    \"    print(\\\"✅ Installed! Testing 'mygrep' command...\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def mygrep(*args, stdin=None):\\n\",","    \"        r = subprocess.run([\\\"mygrep\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"            input=stdin, capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"$ mygrep {' '.join(args)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(r.stdout or f\\\"(exit {r.returncode})\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    mygrep(\\\"Python\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\")\\n\",","    \"    mygrep(\\\"-i\\\", \\\"python\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\", \\\"-c\\\")\\n\",","    \"    mygrep(\\\"-n\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\")\\n\",","    \"    mygrep(\\\"--version\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# ── Package layout explained ─────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"📦 What makes a CLI installable:\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"mygrep/                          ← project root\\n\",","    \"│\\n\",","    \"├── mygrep/                      ← Python package\\n\",","    \"│   ├── __init__.py              ← makes it a package; store __version__\\n\",","    \"│   ├── cli.py                   ← argument parsing + main() entry point\\n\",","    \"│   └── core.py                  ← pure business logic (no I/O)\\n\",","    \"│\\n\",","    \"├── tests/\\n\",","    \"│   └── test_core.py             ← test core.py directly (no CLI needed!)\\n\",","    \"│\\n\",","    \"├── setup.py  OR pyproject.toml  ← declares entry_points / [project.scripts]\\n\",","    \"└── README.md\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"The magic line in setup.py:\\n\",","    \"    entry_points = {\\n\",","    \"        'console_scripts': [\\n\",","    \"            'mygrep = mygrep.cli:main',\\n\",","    \"        ]\\n\",","    \"    }\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"This tells pip: \\\"create a mygrep shell command that calls mygrep.cli.main()\\\"\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"After  pip install -e .  you can run:  $ mygrep pattern file.txt\\n\",","    \"\\\"\\\"\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## Section 10 — Testing Your CLI\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"The best way to test a CLI: test **core logic** as pure functions, and test **CLI behaviour** by invoking via `subprocess`.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import subprocess, sys\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Strategy 1: Test pure core logic directly ─────────────────\\n\",","    \"# No subprocess needed — just import and call functions\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"sys.path.insert(0, \\\"/tmp/mygrep_pkg\\\")\\n\",","    \"from mygrep.core import search_lines\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def assert_equal(label, got, expected):\\n\",","    \"    status = \\\"✅\\\" if got == expected else \\\"❌\\\"\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  {status}  {label}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    if got != expected:\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"       Expected: {expected}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"       Got:      {got}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"lines = [\\\"Hello World\\\\n\\\", \\\"hello python\\\\n\\\", \\\"PYTHON IS GREAT\\\\n\\\", \\\"goodbye\\\\n\\\"]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=== Unit Tests: core.search_lines() ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"results = search_lines(lines, \\\"python\\\")\\n\",","    \"assert_equal(\\\"case-sensitive match\\\", [r[1] for r in results], [\\\"hello python\\\"])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"results = search_lines(lines, \\\"python\\\", ignore_case=True)\\n\",","    \"assert_equal(\\\"case-insensitive match\\\", [r[1] for r in results], [\\\"hello python\\\", \\\"PYTHON IS GREAT\\\"])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"results = search_lines(lines, \\\"python\\\", ignore_case=True, invert=True)\\n\",","    \"assert_equal(\\\"inverted match\\\", [r[1] for r in results], [\\\"Hello World\\\", \\\"goodbye\\\"])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"results = search_lines(lines, \\\"nomatch\\\")\\n\",","    \"assert_equal(\\\"no match returns empty list\\\", results, [])\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# ── Strategy 2: Integration test via subprocess ───────────────\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Integration Tests: CLI via subprocess ===\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def cli_test(label, cmd_args, expected_exit, expected_in_stdout=None, stdin=None):\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"mygrep\\\"] + cmd_args,\\n\",","    \"        capture_output=True, text=True, input=stdin\\n\",","    \"    )\\n\",","    \"    exit_ok    = r.returncode == expected_exit\\n\",","    \"    content_ok = (expected_in_stdout is None) or (expected_in_stdout in r.stdout)\\n\",","    \"    status = \\\"✅\\\" if (exit_ok and content_ok) else \\\"❌\\\"\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"  {status}  {label}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    if not exit_ok:\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"       Exit code: expected {expected_exit}, got {r.returncode}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    if not content_ok:\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"       Expected '{expected_in_stdout}' in output\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"       stdout: {r.stdout[:100]}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"cli_test(\\\"match found → exit 0\\\",\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"-i\\\", \\\"error\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\"], expected_exit=0, expected_in_stdout=\\\"ERROR\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"cli_test(\\\"no match → exit 1\\\",\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"zzznomatch\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\"], expected_exit=1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"cli_test(\\\"count flag\\\",\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"-c\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\"], expected_exit=0, expected_in_stdout=\\\"4\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"cli_test(\\\"stdin mode\\\",\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"hello\\\"], expected_exit=0, expected_in_stdout=\\\"hello\\\",\\n\",","    \"    stdin=\\\"hello world\\\\nfoo bar\\\\n\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"cli_test(\\\"missing file → exit non-zero\\\",\\n\",","    \"    [\\\"pattern\\\", \\\"/tmp/ghost_file.txt\\\"], expected_exit=1)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## 🏁 Mini-Project — `devkit`: A Developer Utilities CLI\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Put everything together. `devkit` is a multi-command CLI that a developer might actually install and use daily.\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"```\\n\",","    \"devkit slug \\\"My Blog Post Title\\\"       → my-blog-post-title\\n\",","    \"devkit hash file.txt [--algo sha256]   → file checksum\\n\",","    \"devkit env check [--required KEY1 KEY2]\\n\",","    \"devkit lines count file.txt\\n\",","    \"devkit lines grep PATTERN file.txt [-i] [-n]\\n\",","    \"devkit json validate file.json\\n\",","    \"devkit json pretty file.json\\n\",","    \"devkit timestamp [--utc] [--format iso]\\n\",","    \"```\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"import textwrap, subprocess, os\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"devkit_script = textwrap.dedent('''\\n\",","    \"    #!/usr/bin/env python3\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    devkit — Developer utility CLI\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    Commands:\\n\",","    \"      devkit slug \u003ctext\u003e               Convert text to a URL slug\\n\",","    \"      devkit hash \u003cfile\u003e [--algo]      Compute file checksum\\n\",","    \"      devkit env check [--required]    Check environment variables\\n\",","    \"      devkit lines count \u003cfile\u003e        Count lines / words / chars\\n\",","    \"      devkit lines grep \u003cpat\u003e \u003cfile\u003e   Search lines in a file\\n\",","    \"      devkit json validate \u003cfile\u003e      Validate JSON syntax\\n\",","    \"      devkit json pretty \u003cfile\u003e        Pretty-print JSON\\n\",","    \"      devkit timestamp                 Current timestamp (various formats)\\n\",","    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"    import argparse, sys, os, hashlib, json, re\\n\",","    \"    from datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    # CORE LOGIC  (pure functions — no I/O, fully testable)\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def make_slug(text):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Convert any text to a URL-safe slug.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        text = text.lower().strip()\\n\",","    \"        text = re.sub(r\\\"[^\\\\w\\\\s-]\\\", \\\"\\\", text)     # remove non-word chars\\n\",","    \"        text = re.sub(r\\\"[\\\\s_]+\\\", \\\"-\\\", text)       # spaces/underscores to hyphen\\n\",","    \"        text = re.sub(r\\\"-+\\\", \\\"-\\\", text)           # collapse multiple hyphens\\n\",","    \"        return text.strip(\\\"-\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def hash_file(path, algo=\\\"sha256\\\"):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Compute a file\\\\'s checksum.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        h = hashlib.new(algo)\\n\",","    \"        with open(path, \\\"rb\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"            for chunk in iter(lambda: f.read(8192), b\\\"\\\"):\\n\",","    \"                h.update(chunk)\\n\",","    \"        return h.hexdigest()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def count_text(text):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Count lines, words, and characters.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        return {\\n\",","    \"            \\\"lines\\\": len(text.splitlines()),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"words\\\": len(text.split()),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"chars\\\": len(text),\\n\",","    \"        }\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def grep_lines(text, pattern, ignore_case=False):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return list of (line_num, line) tuples matching pattern.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        flags   = re.IGNORECASE if ignore_case else 0\\n\",","    \"        return [\\n\",","    \"            (i, line.rstrip())\\n\",","    \"            for i, line in enumerate(text.splitlines(), 1)\\n\",","    \"            if re.search(pattern, line, flags)\\n\",","    \"        ]\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def validate_json_text(text):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return (True, parsed) or (False, error_message).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            return True, json.loads(text)\\n\",","    \"        except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\\n\",","    \"            return False, str(e)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def get_timestamp(utc=False):\\n\",","    \"        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a dict of timestamp formats.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",","    \"        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc) if utc else datetime.now()\\n\",","    \"        return {\\n\",","    \"            \\\"iso\\\":   now.isoformat(),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"unix\\\":  int(now.timestamp()),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"human\\\": now.strftime(\\\"%a %b %d %Y  %H:%M:%S\\\"),\\n\",","    \"            \\\"date\\\":  now.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d\\\"),\\n\",","    \"        }\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    # COMMAND HANDLERS  (I/O layer)\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_slug(args):\\n\",","    \"        text = \\\" \\\".join(args.text)\\n\",","    \"        print(make_slug(text))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_hash(args):\\n\",","    \"        supported = [\\\"md5\\\", \\\"sha1\\\", \\\"sha256\\\", \\\"sha512\\\"]\\n\",","    \"        if args.algo not in supported:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: unsupported algorithm \\\\'{args.algo}\\\\'. Use: {supported}\\\",\\n\",","    \"                  file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            digest = hash_file(args.file, args.algo)\\n\",","    \"            if args.check:\\n\",","    \"                if digest == args.check:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"✅ Checksum verified: {digest}\\\")\\n\",","    \"                else:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"❌ Checksum MISMATCH\\\")\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"   Expected: {args.check}\\\")\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"   Got:      {digest}\\\")\\n\",","    \"                    sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"            else:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"{digest}  {args.file}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: file not found: {args.file}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_env_check(args):\\n\",","    \"        required = args.required or []\\n\",","    \"        optional = args.optional or []\\n\",","    \"        all_vars = required + optional\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if not all_vars:\\n\",","    \"            # Show all env vars\\n\",","    \"            for k, v in sorted(os.environ.items()):\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"  {k}={v[:40] + \\\\'...\\\\' if len(v) \u003e 40 else v}\\\")\\n\",","    \"            return\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        missing = []\\n\",","    \"        for var in required:\\n\",","    \"            val = os.getenv(var)\\n\",","    \"            icon = \\\"✅\\\" if val else \\\"❌\\\"\\n\",","    \"            display = val[:30] + \\\"...\\\" if val and len(val) \u003e 30 else (val or \\\"(not set)\\\")\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {icon}  {var:\u003c25} {display}\\\")\\n\",","    \"            if not val:\\n\",","    \"                missing.append(var)\\n\",","    \"        for var in optional:\\n\",","    \"            val = os.getenv(var)\\n\",","    \"            icon = \\\"✅\\\" if val else \\\"⚪\\\"\\n\",","    \"            display = val[:30] + \\\"...\\\" if val and len(val) \u003e 30 else (val or \\\"(not set)\\\")\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"  {icon}  {var:\u003c25} {display}  [optional]\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        if missing:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"\\\\n  ❌ {len(missing)} required variable(s) missing: {\\\\', \\\\'.join(missing)}\\\",\\n\",","    \"                  file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            print(\\\"\\\\n  ✅ All required env vars present.\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_lines_count(args):\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            with open(args.file) as f:\\n\",","    \"                text = f.read()\\n\",","    \"        except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: {args.file} not found\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        stats = count_text(text)\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  Lines:  {stats[\\\\'lines\\\\']:\u003e8}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  Words:  {stats[\\\\'words\\\\']:\u003e8}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        print(f\\\"  Chars:  {stats[\\\\'chars\\\\']:\u003e8}\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_lines_grep(args):\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            src = open(args.file) if args.file else sys.stdin\\n\",","    \"            text = src.read()\\n\",","    \"        except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: {args.file} not found\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        matches = grep_lines(text, args.pattern, args.ignore_case)\\n\",","    \"        if not matches:\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"        for lineno, line in matches:\\n\",","    \"            if args.line_numbers:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"{lineno:\u003e4}: {line}\\\")\\n\",","    \"            else:\\n\",","    \"                print(line)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_json_validate(args):\\n\",","    \"        for path in args.files:\\n\",","    \"            try:\\n\",","    \"                with open(path) as f:\\n\",","    \"                    text = f.read()\\n\",","    \"                ok, result = validate_json_text(text)\\n\",","    \"                if ok:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"  ✅ {path}  —  valid JSON\\\")\\n\",","    \"                else:\\n\",","    \"                    print(f\\\"  ❌ {path}  —  {result}\\\")\\n\",","    \"            except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"  ⚠️  {path}  —  file not found\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_json_pretty(args):\\n\",","    \"        try:\\n\",","    \"            with open(args.file) as f:\\n\",","    \"                text = f.read()\\n\",","    \"            ok, result = validate_json_text(text)\\n\",","    \"            if not ok:\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"Error: invalid JSON: {result}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"                sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"            indent = args.indent\\n\",","    \"            pretty = json.dumps(result, indent=indent, sort_keys=args.sort_keys)\\n\",","    \"            if args.output:\\n\",","    \"                with open(args.output, \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"                    f.write(pretty)\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"Written to {args.output}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            else:\\n\",","    \"                print(pretty)\\n\",","    \"        except FileNotFoundError:\\n\",","    \"            print(f\\\"Error: {args.file} not found\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\",","    \"            sys.exit(1)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def cmd_timestamp(args):\\n\",","    \"        ts = get_timestamp(utc=args.utc)\\n\",","    \"        if args.format == \\\"all\\\":\\n\",","    \"            for fmt, val in ts.items():\\n\",","    \"                print(f\\\"  {fmt:\u003c8} {val}\\\")\\n\",","    \"        else:\\n\",","    \"            print(ts.get(args.format, ts[\\\"iso\\\"]))\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"    # ARGUMENT PARSER\\n\",","    \"    # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def build_parser():\\n\",","    \"        parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\\n\",","    \"            prog=\\\"devkit\\\",\\n\",","    \"            description=\\\"🛠️  Developer utility toolkit\\\",\\n\",","    \"            formatter_class=argparse.RawDescriptionHelpFormatter\\n\",","    \"        )\\n\",","    \"        parser.add_argument(\\\"--version\\\", action=\\\"version\\\", version=\\\"devkit 1.0.0\\\")\\n\",","    \"        subs = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"command\\\", metavar=\\\"COMMAND\\\")\\n\",","    \"        subs.required = True\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # slug\\n\",","    \"        p = subs.add_parser(\\\"slug\\\", help=\\\"Convert text to a URL slug\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"text\\\", nargs=\\\"+\\\", help=\\\"Text to slugify\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.set_defaults(func=cmd_slug)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # hash\\n\",","    \"        p = subs.add_parser(\\\"hash\\\", help=\\\"Compute file checksum\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"file\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"--algo\\\", default=\\\"sha256\\\",\\n\",","    \"            choices=[\\\"md5\\\",\\\"sha1\\\",\\\"sha256\\\",\\\"sha512\\\"])\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"--check\\\", metavar=\\\"HASH\\\",\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Verify file matches this hash\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.set_defaults(func=cmd_hash)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # env\\n\",","    \"        p_env = subs.add_parser(\\\"env\\\", help=\\\"Inspect environment variables\\\")\\n\",","    \"        env_subs = p_env.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"env_cmd\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_ec = env_subs.add_parser(\\\"check\\\", help=\\\"Check required env vars\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_ec.add_argument(\\\"--required\\\", nargs=\\\"+\\\", metavar=\\\"VAR\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_ec.add_argument(\\\"--optional\\\", nargs=\\\"+\\\", metavar=\\\"VAR\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_ec.set_defaults(func=cmd_env_check)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # lines\\n\",","    \"        p_lines = subs.add_parser(\\\"lines\\\", help=\\\"Work with text file lines\\\")\\n\",","    \"        lines_subs = p_lines.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"lines_cmd\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_lc = lines_subs.add_parser(\\\"count\\\", help=\\\"Count lines/words/chars\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lc.add_argument(\\\"file\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lc.set_defaults(func=cmd_lines_count)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_lg = lines_subs.add_parser(\\\"grep\\\", help=\\\"Search lines\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lg.add_argument(\\\"pattern\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lg.add_argument(\\\"file\\\", nargs=\\\"?\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lg.add_argument(\\\"-i\\\", \\\"--ignore-case\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lg.add_argument(\\\"-n\\\", \\\"--line-numbers\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_lg.set_defaults(func=cmd_lines_grep)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # json\\n\",","    \"        p_json = subs.add_parser(\\\"json\\\", help=\\\"JSON utilities\\\")\\n\",","    \"        json_subs = p_json.add_subparsers(dest=\\\"json_cmd\\\")\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_jv = json_subs.add_parser(\\\"validate\\\", help=\\\"Validate JSON files\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jv.add_argument(\\\"files\\\", nargs=\\\"+\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jv.set_defaults(func=cmd_json_validate)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        p_jp = json_subs.add_parser(\\\"pretty\\\", help=\\\"Pretty-print JSON\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jp.add_argument(\\\"file\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jp.add_argument(\\\"--indent\\\", type=int, default=2)\\n\",","    \"        p_jp.add_argument(\\\"--sort-keys\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jp.add_argument(\\\"--output\\\", \\\"-o\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p_jp.set_defaults(func=cmd_json_pretty)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        # timestamp\\n\",","    \"        p = subs.add_parser(\\\"timestamp\\\", aliases=[\\\"ts\\\"],\\n\",","    \"            help=\\\"Show current timestamp\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"--utc\\\", action=\\\"store_true\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.add_argument(\\\"--format\\\", choices=[\\\"iso\\\",\\\"unix\\\",\\\"human\\\",\\\"date\\\",\\\"all\\\"],\\n\",","    \"            default=\\\"all\\\")\\n\",","    \"        p.set_defaults(func=cmd_timestamp)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"        return parser\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    def main():\\n\",","    \"        parser = build_parser()\\n\",","    \"        args = parser.parse_args()\\n\",","    \"        args.func(args)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"    if __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n\",","    \"        main()\\n\",","    \"''')\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"with open(\\\"/tmp/devkit.py\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\",","    \"    f.write(devkit_script)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"def devkit(*args, stdin=None, env=None):\\n\",","    \"    environment = os.environ.copy()\\n\",","    \"    if env:\\n\",","    \"        environment.update(env)\\n\",","    \"    r = subprocess.run(\\n\",","    \"        [\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/devkit.py\\\"] + list(args),\\n\",","    \"        capture_output=True, text=True, input=stdin, env=environment\\n\",","    \"    )\\n\",","    \"    print(f\\\"$ devkit {' '.join(args)}\\\")\\n\",","    \"    print(r.stdout or r.stderr)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 55)\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"  🛠️  devkit — LIVE DEMO\\\")\\n\",","    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 55)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"slug\\\", \\\"My Awesome Blog Post Title 2024!\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"slug\\\", \\\"Hello   World  --  Special \u0026 Characters\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"hash\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"hash\\\", \\\"/tmp/article.txt\\\", \\\"--algo\\\", \\\"md5\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"lines\\\", \\\"count\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"lines\\\", \\\"grep\\\", \\\"ERROR\\\", \\\"/tmp/server.log\\\", \\\"-n\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"json\\\", \\\"validate\\\", \\\"/tmp/config.json\\\", \\\"/tmp/bad.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"json\\\", \\\"pretty\\\", \\\"/tmp/config.json\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"timestamp\\\")\\n\",","    \"devkit(\\\"env\\\", \\\"check\\\", \\\"--required\\\", \\\"HOME\\\", \\\"PATH\\\", \\\"MISSING_VAR\\\")\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"### 🚀 Mini-Project Challenges\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"Extend `devkit` with these commands:\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"**Challenge A — `devkit uuid`**\\n\",","    \"Print a random UUID. Use Python's built-in `uuid` module.\\n\",","    \"- `--count N` — generate N UUIDs\\n\",","    \"- `--format hex|short|full` — different output styles\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"**Challenge B — `devkit base64`**\\n\",","    \"Encode or decode base64 from a string or file.\\n\",","    \"- `devkit base64 encode \\\"hello world\\\"`\\n\",","    \"- `devkit base64 decode \\\"aGVsbG8gd29ybGQ=\\\"`\\n\",","    \"- `devkit base64 encode --file photo.jpg` (reads from file)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"**Challenge C — `devkit template`**\\n\",","    \"Simple string templating from key=value pairs:\\n\",","    \"- `devkit template \\\"Hello {{name}}, your order #{{id}} is ready!\\\" name=Alice id=1042`\\n\",","    \"- Outputs: `Hello Alice, your order #1042 is ready!`\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"**Challenge D — `devkit diff` (Bonus)**\\n\",","    \"Compare two text files and print a simple diff (lines only in file1, only in file2, common lines). Use Python's `difflib` module.\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"code\",","   \"execution_count\": null,","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"outputs\": [],","   \"source\": [","    \"# Challenge A — uuid command\\n\",","    \"# Hint: import uuid; uuid.uuid4()\\n\",","    \"# Add to build_parser() and write cmd_uuid(args)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Challenge B — base64 command  \\n\",","    \"# Hint: import base64; base64.b64encode(), base64.b64decode()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Challenge C — template command\\n\",","    \"# Hint: re.sub(r'\\\\{\\\\{(\\\\w+)\\\\}\\\\}', lambda m: kwargs.get(m.group(1), m.group(0)), template)\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Challenge D — diff command\\n\",","    \"# Hint: import difflib; difflib.unified_diff()\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"# Write your extended devkit to /tmp/devkit2.py and test it below\\n\",","    \"# r = subprocess.run([\\\"python3\\\", \\\"/tmp/devkit2.py\\\", \\\"uuid\\\", \\\"--count\\\", \\\"3\\\"],\\n\",","    \"#                    capture_output=True, text=True)\\n\",","    \"# print(r.stdout)\"","   ]","  },","  {","   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",","   \"metadata\": {},","   \"source\": [","    \"---\\n\",","    \"## ✅ What You've Learned\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"| Topic | Skill | Real Example Built |\\n\",","    \"|-------|-------|-------------------|\\n\",","    \"| **Anatomy** | `main()`, `if __name__`, pure functions | `greet.py` |\\n\",","    \"| **`sys.argv`** | Raw arg parsing, validation | `wordcount.py` |\\n\",","    \"| **`argparse`** | Flags, types, choices, help | `loganalyser.py` |\\n\",","    \"| **Subcommands** | Git-style multi-command CLIs | `proj.py` task manager |\\n\",","    \"| **stdin/stdout/stderr** | Pipes, redirection, Unix philosophy | `txtool.py` pipeline |\\n\",","    \"| **Exit codes** | Success/failure signalling for CI/CD | `healthcheck.py` |\\n\",","    \"| **Config layering** | defaults → file → env → CLI | `datapipe.py` |\\n\",","    \"| **Rich output** | Progress bars, colour, tables | bulk file processor |\\n\",","    \"| **Packaging** | `entry_points`, `setup.py`, installable | `mygrep` package |\\n\",","    \"| **Testing** | Unit tests on core, integration via subprocess | `test_mygrep` |\\n\",","    \"| **Mini-project** | Full multi-command developer toolkit | `devkit.py` |\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"---\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"### 📚 What to Learn Next\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"- **`click`** — A higher-level CLI framework (decorator-based, very clean)\\n\",","    \"- **`typer`** — Like `click` but powered by Python type hints (autocomplete!)\\n\",","    \"- **`rich`** — Beautiful terminal output: tables, markdown, syntax highlighting\\n\",","    \"- **`tqdm`** — The standard progress-bar library\\n\",","    \"- **`pytest`** — The standard test runner for proper test suites\\n\",","    \"- **`pipx`** — Install Python CLI tools in isolated environments\\n\",","    \"- **`shiv` / `PyInstaller`** — Bundle a CLI into a single executable file\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"---\\n\",","    \"\\n\",","    \"\u003e 💡 *Every tool you use daily — `git`, `docker`, `aws`, `npm`, `kubectl` — started as a script like the ones in this notebook. The only difference is years of polish.*\"","   ]","  }"," ],"," \"metadata\": {","  \"kernelspec\": {","   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",","   \"language\": \"python\",","   \"name\": \"python3\"","  },","  \"lang